<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1916,2015]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,1581]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="4" pageNumber="367">Head black with the following markings of golden scales: a) a patch from median groove of rostrum spreading backwards to outline inner edge of eyes; b) a lateral spot under eye and anterior to gena. Rostrum rugose, as long as wide, bearing very short yellowish hairs on dorsal and latero-ventral surfaces; dorsal surface with shallow median groove. Eyes medium-sized, moderately protruding. Antennal scape as long as funicle, with scattered yellowish setae. Funicular segment I four times longer than wide, one-quarter length of II; segments III–VII as long as wide; club sub-ellipsoidal, nearly three times longer than wide.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098856" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5098856" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5098856/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" startId="5.[151,250,1955,1979]" targetBox="[209,1378,192,1917]" targetPageId="5">
