– 
<quantity box="[302,380,870,897]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2mm</quantity>
(ā 
<quantity box="[416,514,871,898]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.66" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" unit="mm" value="4.66">4.66mm</quantity>
). N=5
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1581]" box="[199,587,907,933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation box="[433,583,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,885,1589]" captionTargetId="figure-295@3.[151,1435,885,1589]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia of Metapocyrtus waoensis sp. nov. A. penis in dorsal view, B. idem in lateral view, C. sternite IX in dorsal view, Male genitalia of Metapocyrtus lanaoensis sp. nov. D. penis in dorsal view, E. idem in lateral view, F. sternite IX in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098850" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5098850/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Figure 2C–D</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Otherwise similar to male, with the following distinctions: Pronotum slightly shorter than in male. Elytra wider and longer than in male; with two tufts of robust brownish dense and erect bristles located at apex of declivity (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[209,1378,192,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[192,1396,181,1931]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. A: Metapocyrtus lanaoensis sp. nov. Holotype; B: idem, lateral view; C: Metapocyrtus lanaoensis sp. nov. female; C1: tuft of bristles at the apex of elytral declivity; D: idem, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098856" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5098856/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Figure 4C</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[227,235,1014,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[228,1366,196,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-28@2.[210,1378,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: Metapocyrtus waoensis sp. nov. Holotype; B: idem, lateral view; C: Metapocyrtus waoensis sp. nov. female; C1: tuft of bristles at the apex of elytral declivity; D: idem, lateral view; E–H: idem, variability." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5098846/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
<superScript attach="left" box="[227,235,1014,1028]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">1</superScript>
</figureCitation>
). Ventrite I simple, not depressed. Tarsi narrower.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,594,1050,1077]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Notes on variability in markings.</emphasis>
About 40% of the specimens have an additional elytral strip on interval II, extending from behind the middle, and about 30% of the specimens have all scales of the same golden color.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
