<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="369" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1482,1508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Distribution.</emphasis>
The new species is restricted to the South-Eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[921,1080,1483,1509]" country="Philippines" name="Lanao del Sur" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Lanao del Sur</collectingRegion>
, Mindanao. No specimens were ever obtained from nearby well-sampled areas like Northern 
<collectingRegion box="[834,1116,1519,1545]" country="Philippines" name="North Cotabato" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">North Cotabato Province</collectingRegion>
, which share part of fauna.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1302,1555,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1581]" box="[199,1302,1555,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1555,1581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is a participle, in the genitive case, meaning “of Lanao”.
</paragraph>
